The best wallets for your Crypto 2023, is your wallet on the list?:

Trust Wallet ( @TrustWallet ): Trust wallet is top of my list because it is owned by Binance who I personally feel are one of if not the most reputable company in crypto. 

It is super easy to use, supports a huge range of Cryptos with high security.

Trust wallet is my go-to mobile wallet, with a built in web3 browser and it is non-custodial which is superb as that means nobody has knowledge of or access to your private keys. 

Metamask ( @MetaMask ): Metamask is also a wallet I use, in my opinion it isn’t a million miles away from Trust wallet, but lacks the ability to store Bitcoin which is my largest asset holding. 

Metamask has over 30 million active users and is known for its reliability, security and is also non-custodial. 

Finally, I would go with the Cryptocom wallet ( @cryptocom ), with a strong security presence using biometrics and Secure Enclave tech on IOS devices. They also have an interest system for around 20 crypto’s. 

Again backed by a reputable exchange which makes it all the more appealing in my eyes. Note that you don’t have to have an account on the exchange. 

Overall, this is not financial advice and you should do your own research before using any of the mentioned wallets.

✅𝐒𝐄𝐂 𝐯𝐬 𝐑𝐢𝐜𝐡𝐚𝐫𝐝 𝐇𝐞𝐚𝐫𝐭 (𝐖𝐚𝐫 𝐀𝐠𝐚𝐢𝐧𝐬𝐭 𝐂𝐫𝐲𝐩𝐭𝐨, 𝐅𝐫𝐞𝐞𝐝𝐨𝐦 𝐨𝐟 𝐒𝐩𝐞𝐞𝐜𝐡, & 𝐑𝐢𝐠𝐡𝐭 𝐭𝐨 𝐓𝐫𝐚𝐧𝐬𝐚𝐜𝐭)

First they ignore you
Then they laugh at you
Then they fight you
Then you win - TBD

🔹𝐖𝐡𝐚𝐭'𝐬 𝐚𝐭 𝐬𝐭𝐚𝐤𝐞?

This case will go down in history. Richard Heart has the attention of crypto and the world. 

There is more to this case than meets the eye. One may be mistaken in thinking this case is soley about Richard Heart, HEX, PulseChain and PulseX. Whoever wins this case will set legal precedent in crypto law for years to come. This means projects like Ethereum and such are at risk as well in the scenario that a bad precedent is set. It is evident that the government wants to gain control over things like crypto. Whether you were an investor in Ripple (XRP) or not, if you enjoy crypto freedom, then everyone ought to stand behind them, support them, and root for them. Recently they were victorious against the SEC in their multi year long lawsuit. The same applies to this case. If freedom of speech, & the right to transact is important to you - everyone in crypto should be rooting for Richard Heart. 

🔹𝐔𝐧𝐟𝐚𝐢𝐫 𝐓𝐚𝐫𝐠𝐞𝐭𝐭𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐨𝐟 𝐇𝐄𝐗 (𝐔𝐧𝐢𝐬𝐰𝐚𝐩)

Imagine you are Hayden Adams (the creator of Uniswap). You have just built a revolutionary 'decentralized' product where people can buy and sell crypto in a permissionless way. Richard Heart popularizes your product by telling all the Hexicans about your invention. In the process countless people in the HEX community end up getting the UNI airdrop. HEX becomes responsible for some of the highest amount of volume and activity on-chain helping your project and spreading the word. Yesterday, Uniswap marked HEX as an "unsupported asset". For lack of better terms, Uniswap single handedly spit on Richard Heart and HEX for helping them out in the early days. To make matters worse they consider themselves to be decentralized, and yet specifically target HEX. What's your problem Hayden Adams, do you dislike Richard Heart? Do you dislike HEX investors? Do you not believe in decentralization? This is simply an attack, shame on Uniswap. Uniswap has not acted when there were obvious scams and rugpulls, but specifically targets HEX today. 

🔹𝐑𝐢𝐜𝐡𝐚𝐫𝐝 𝐇𝐞𝐚𝐫𝐭

As an outsider it is very easy to dislike or not understand someone like Richard Heart. Why do I say this? Because I thought he was a scammer and I didn't trust him at first. Imagine someone tuning in for the first time and seeing a man with designer cloths twerking talking about crypto. This typically isn't the type of person you'd want to take seriously. However, if you take the time to dig deeper you will be shocked. In my opinion Richard Heart is one of the brighest minds in crypto who really cares about the small guys as well as our primary basic rights of freedom. In specific the freedom of speech and the right to transact are very relevant to this case. Richard Heart is the type of person where if you just listen for ten minutes, you will gain a wealth of knowledge and perspectives that you may have never thought of. How do I know this? I've spent countless hours watching his highly engaging videos. I am not sure whether the SEC underestimates the wit of Richard Heart, but I believe he is easily top three best to represent crypto. 

🔹𝐖𝐡𝐲 𝐝𝐨𝐞𝐬 𝐑𝐢𝐜𝐡𝐚𝐫𝐝 𝐇𝐞𝐚𝐫𝐭 𝐭𝐰𝐞𝐫𝐤 𝐢𝐧 𝐝𝐞𝐬𝐢𝐠𝐧𝐞𝐫 𝐜𝐥𝐨𝐭𝐡𝐬?!

Simply put - outrage marketing. Every action is strategic and surgical. In his older videos he has mentioned that he would wear a black t-shirt and speak his mind. Unfortunately this wasn't enough to get the proper amount of attention and eyes to do what he always wanted to accomplish. One of his goals was to make the best crypto built for the greatest price appreciation the world had ever seen. He was very successful in business before crypto, and even mined BTC blocks for cents back in the early days of Bitcoin. It's not about the money for him - his ultimate goal is legacy, glory, but most importantly love from his peers. 

I have tracked down 6+ older clips of Richard admitting that the stuff he does and wears is completely ridiculous. It's just about getting as many eyes as possible, then for those who stick around educating and teaching them about stuff that actually matters. To put into perspective how effective this tactic is, Richard single handedly tripled his Twitter follower count in the midst of the bear market. Plenty of clips and memes were created in the process - genius marketing. 

What I'm trying to say is the guy in designer isn't Richard Heart at all. Unfortunately that's what gets peoples attention, and he is the type of person to do whatever it takes to accomplish his goals. Months ago he has pivoted to being "humble". This was the real Richard Heart all along. I totally understand why some people dislike him, but I don't think they have met the real Richard. 

🔹𝐈𝐭 𝐝𝐨𝐞𝐬𝐧'𝐭 𝐦𝐚𝐭𝐭𝐞𝐫 𝐢𝐟 𝐲𝐨𝐮 𝐝𝐢𝐬𝐥𝐢𝐤𝐞 𝐑𝐢𝐜𝐡𝐚𝐫𝐝 𝐇𝐞𝐚𝐫𝐭

This case is about crypto precedent, the freedom of speech, and the fundamental right to transact. Richard Heart doesn't work for you, doesn't work for us, doesn't work for anyone. It's just you and the smart contract code when it comes to his project(s). 

🔹𝐂𝐚𝐧 𝐂𝐫𝐲𝐩𝐭𝐨 𝐛𝐞 𝐬𝐭𝐨𝐩𝐩𝐞𝐝?

Fortunately you can't control immutable code, decentralization, smart contracts without admin keys, with validators spread all over the world supporting the network. Every action done on the blockchain is recorded forever on a spreadsheet we call the blockchain. This is essentially what Richard Heart has built with projects like HEX, PulseChain and PulseX. 

🔹𝐖𝐚𝐭𝐜𝐡 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐦𝐨𝐯𝐢𝐞! 𝐓𝐡𝐞 𝐇𝐢𝐠𝐡𝐞𝐬𝐭 𝐨𝐟 𝐒𝐭𝐚𝐤𝐞𝐬

In the captivating documentary 'Highest of Stakes,' viewers are taken on an exhilarating journey alongside renowned entrepreneur Richard Heart as he embarks on a groundbreaking mission to revolutionize the world of finance. Fueled by his unwavering belief in the potential of blockchain technology, Heart sets out to create a game-changing network called HEX and PulseChain.

🔹𝐋𝐞𝐭 𝐦𝐞 𝐤𝐧𝐨𝐰 𝐰𝐡𝐚𝐭 𝐲𝐨𝐮 𝐠𝐮𝐲𝐬 𝐭𝐡𝐢𝐧𝐤!

I want to know your thoughts. Feel free to educate me, add stuff, love me, or hate me.

These are just my opinions, nothing is stated as fact. 

Make sure to like, comment, retweet!
If you made it this far don't forget to follow and bell button!😎👽❤🚀⚡

responsible for some of the highest amount of volume and activity on-chain helping your project and spreading the word. yesterday, uniswap marked hex as an "unsupported asset". for lack of better terms, uniswap single handedly spit on richard heart and hex for helping them out in the early days. to make matters worse they consider themselves to be decentralized, and yet specifically target hex. what's your problem hayden adams, do you dislike richard heart? do you dislike hex investors? do you not believe in decentralization? this is simply an attack, shame on uniswap. uniswap has not acted when there were obvious scams and rugpulls, but specifically targets hex today. :small_blue_diamond: 𝐑𝐢𝐜𝐡𝐚𝐫𝐝 𝐇𝐞𝐚𝐫𝐭 as an outsider it is very easy to dislike or not understand someone like richard heart. why do i say this? because i thought he was a scammer and i didn't trust him at first. imagine someone tuning in for the first time and seeing a man with designer cloths twerking talking about crypto. this typically isn't the type of person you'd want to take seriously. however, if you take the time to dig deeper you will be shocked. in my opinion richard heart is one of the brighest minds in crypto who really cares about the small guys as well as our primary basic rights of freedom. in specific the freedom of speech and the right to transact are very relevant to this case. richard heart is the type of person where if you just listen for ten minutes, you will gain a wealth of knowledge and perspectives that you may have never thought of. how do i know this? i've spent countless hours watching his highly engaging videos. i am not sure whether the sec underestimates the wit of richard heart, but i believe he is easily top three best to represent crypto. :small_blue_diamond: 𝐖𝐡𝐲 𝐝𝐨𝐞𝐬 𝐑𝐢𝐜𝐡𝐚𝐫𝐝 𝐇𝐞𝐚𝐫𝐭 𝐭𝐰𝐞𝐫𝐤 𝐢𝐧 𝐝𝐞𝐬𝐢𝐠𝐧𝐞𝐫 𝐜𝐥𝐨𝐭𝐡𝐬?! simply put - outrage marketing. every action is strategic and surgical. in his older videos he has mentioned that he would wear a black t-shirt and speak his mind. unfortunately this wasn't enough to get the proper amount of attention and eyes to do what he always wanted to accomplish. one of his goals was to make the best crypto built for the greatest price appreciation the world had ever seen. he was very successful in business before crypto, and even mined btc blocks for cents back in the early days of bitcoin. it's not about the money for him - his ultimate goal is legacy, glory, but most importantly love from his peers. i have tracked down 6+ older clips of richard admitting that the stuff he does and wears is completely ridiculous. it's just about getting as many eyes as possible, then for those who stick around educating and teaching them about stuff that actually matters. to put into perspective how effective this tactic is, richard single handedly tripled his twitter follower count in the midst of the bear market. plenty of clips and memes were created in the process - genius marketing. what i'm trying to say is the guy in designer isn't richard heart at all. unfortunately that's what gets peoples attention, and he is the type of person to do whatever it takes to accomplish his goals. months I'll be frank, I don't wish for #Bitcoin to skyrocket because I favor affordable sats. Yet, there's a limit to how many weak hands can offer cheap sats before they're all scooped up. Hence, a #BTC surge seems inevitable.

#Bitcoin is attracting a lot of attention now. Some are trying to time the market, others prioritize time in the market. The latter will likely reap the most rewards.

It's mostly short-term holders who are selling. Long-term holders see #BTC as their exit strategy.

I predict several liquidity crunches in #Bitcoin's trading volume, followed by rallies. If the current demand materializes, I suspect we're all underestimating the bullish potential. If not, I'll appreciate the chance to accumulate more #BTC at lower prices. I plan to keep stacking, setting aside only what I don't need right now, in hopes of a brighter future!

Oftentimes, newly minted plebs will stack a modest amount of sats, and then simply sit on their hands and *wait* for hyperbitcoinization to occur.

Juneseth refers to this phenomenon as “Bitcoin purgatory.”

Do not fall into this trap. Instead, save in Bitcoin and focus on your craft. The more productive each of us are, the sooner the world adopts a Bitcoin standard.

Don’t forget to enjoy life as well. Remember, it’s about the journey.

"If silver is gonna 1000x, I will walk into my kitchen right now, I will melt all my silverware, and I will sell it at market.   

If gold is gonna rally, Elon Musk will find more on Mars. This is a super important point...  

#Bitcoin is the only monetary instrument in the history of our species that is fixed. It does not matter how much more demand comes into the asset class, no one will ever be able to make more of it.  

There are 2 things I can guarantee you in my life:   

- That I’ll die  
- There will only ever be 21 million Bitcoin   

And those are the 2 things that I can only value; is my life and my Bitcoin.   

So it is the only fixed supply asset, it’s not that complicated. It’s gonna go up because everything else can be issued more.  

The only thing that is clear to us and clear to our customers is that you cannot hold and save in dollars anymore.   

I think there is going to be a new era of the US dollar where inflation will enter and normalize 5, 6, 7, 8, 9, 10%. The days of 2% inflation are over. The FED really blew this thing up.  

You can call it inflation because the CPI is a load of nonsense, right? Like the government is going to tell me how the dollar is inflating based on a basket of instruments.   

Like my Netflix subscription or my Caesar salad doesn’t actually tell me how well the dollar is doing or how much it’s being devalued.   

Miami real estate does, Bitcoin does. Bitcoin is up over 50% this year. You’re telling me the dollar isn’t inflating? You’re out of your mind. I’m not listening to that.  

The FED and the whole monetary system is based on trust and they constantly, they constantly break that trust.   

It would be the equivalent to there’s a fire outside my house, I smell the smoke and someone tells me, “No no no it’s a bunch of teenagers putting on a bonfire.”   

Okay, but I hear one police siren, are you sure it’s a bonfire? “Yea, yea yea it’s a bonfire.” Now I hear 10 sirens, 100 sirens, now my whole community is running out.   

I’m not gonna get up and look outside the window and see what’s going on? I don’t believe them for a second, you have to be absolutely crazy to believe the federal reserve right now. They’re full of it and I don’t have to because I own Bitcoin.  

There’s no one that can deflate my instrument. I get to hold it, save in it, I know the monetary policy, I sleep like a baby, like the baby face that I am.   

I think you’re crazy to believe the FED and these swap lines and treating these assets at par. It’s a gimmick, it’s a scam." -@JackMallers⚡

cleaned_data.original_text:
If #bitcoin launched with all 21,000,000 coins and only reduced its Supply over time, do you think it would be at a much higher price now?

You can think of Supply as the enemy of price. 

If you get all the Supply into the world at once you can washout the weakest hands faster.

Some coins instead of INFLATING(more to sell later) they actually DEFLATE(less to sell later) over time. 

PulseX is one of those coins. 1.7% of the User Owned Supply has been bought and burned forever in only 3 months.(On bear market volume I might add)

Imagine 357,000 BTC being burned at todays prices.
That would be over $10.7 Billion dollars worth.

When PLSX gets to $0.03 per token then this 1.7% will be worth $10.7 Billion as well. It's a long game. (1883x)

353 Billion PLSX(1.7%) can be bought today for around $5.68 Million. (Limit Order)

Over 396 days(13 months~) Bitcoin inflates to create 1.7% of 21M Supply(357,000 BTC) 
Remember that Supply is the Enemy of Price.

Meanwhile in just 90 days PLSX has REMOVED 1.7% of its Supply. Put another way, In less than 1/4th of the time it took for Bitcoin to create 1.7% MORE SUPPLY, we have actually reduced our Supply by 1.7%.

This #Bitcoin chart from 2019...

I used to stare at it every day thinking to myself

"Will this Bitcoin thing eventually go back up in price or has the bubble popped for good?"

I only bought small amounts at the time because I thought it was risky

If I had taken 20 hours to understand Bitcoin's fundamentals, I would have invested much more of my paycheck into bitcoin

And I'd have ALOT more than I do today

So I'm buying large amounts

The more time you spend learning about Bitcoin is directly correlated to how much you buy

Learn. Buy. Hold.

Your future self will thank you when Bitcoin reaches new all-time highs

cleaned_data.original_text:
This may be one of the last times to load up before the next bull cycle

From $15k to $31k, $BTC has been on a hell of a run since Nov 22.. but we are now seeing signs of weakness in motion

This is par for the course for #bitcoin going into its four year halvening schedule

$BTC bottoms.. an impressive bounce.. retracement into/before halvening.. bull run post halvening

With data suggesting a larger pullback on the horizon for the global economy resulting in a recession.. it may swing the scales slightly in the favour of a #crypto retracement over the next 6-9 months

But.. this is where a wealth of opportunity lies

If you have not experienced a true bull cycle before.. then boy, are you in for a shock..

With #bitcoin usually leading the charge from the front-line, an abundance of liquidity pours its way into the space.. once that liquidity is here, it spills into nearly every area of #crypto 

Many will make impressive returns during this period.. whether that be through cunning or luck..

But those who will maximize their gains are those who are positioned BEFORE the bull cycle even begins

This is where the beauty lies within a bear market.. 

Of course they can be brutal and costly for most, but if you are able to find the right project at the right price.. it can be life changing

In a bear market, no one is watching.. the large majority of people have thrown in the towel and its left to the nerds to stick to their hobby of playing with magic internet money in their moms basements.. but those people who scampered for the door will return

They will make up the crowd who begin to take notice once again when they start hearing on the news about #bitcoin approaching new ATHs.. or their friend boasting about how their son managed to buy a new sports car with money he made from this hot new #crypto called $ETH.. or was it $XRP? I can't remember what she told me.. 

When nobody gives a shit.. that's when you should be paying the most attention

If you are reading this, then that means you are, so congrats.. because you are here right when it matters the most

Most projects don't become bad projects because the price is lower than it was 12 months ago.. in fact, they are most likely better thanks to a year of full on development

With all the attention gone.. price in the dumps.. and real tangible growth.. it offers a unique once in a lifetime opportunity

Of course, most projects will still be dogshit.. but sprinkled in that pile of muck will be true fundamental gems..

These are what you are seeking.. and you should be seeking them when no-one else is watching

Yes.. people will make great gains when bullish conditions return.. but positioning near the bottom will allow you to increase the percentage of gains by a staggering amount

Positioning now will most likely still look like a genius move at the top of the next cycle..

But.. this may be the last dip we get before the next cycle begins, and that is where the pot of gold is sitting at the end of the rainbow

Bargain bucket prices on the menu before a sea of liquidity enters the market.. it makes the mouth water, huh?

Now, of course.. the dip may not come and $BTC may continue on its upward trajectory, nor do I think we take out the lows of $15.5k.. but if you have capital available to tackle any upcoming market retracement, then now may be the time to strategize on identifying projects you want to own for the entirety of the next bull cycle

I have price levels set on entries I would like on strong fundamental projects like $TAO, $KAS, $QNT.. ones I think will outperform the rest of the market in a large way going forward

Also.. projects I perceive to be largely undervalued like $CHEQ, $MC, $FACT, $BBANK etc

But.. you need to identify your own projects, following your own strategies.. What you look for in a project may not be what I look for.. and vice-versa

The point is.. we may be entering a time of maximum opportunity

So.. if you don't have a plan drawn up of how to tackle this next 6-9 month period and beyond..

I suggest creating a fucking plan.. you won't regret it

cleaned_data.original_text:
I think some of you can identify with the following: 

I came to #Bitcoin because I wanted to make money. Completely unaware of the consequences this decision would have on my future and certainly the rest of my life, the initial incentive to get closer to financial freedom very quickly turned into my world view being taken in hand, dropped and broken into a thousand parts that were rearranged by Bitcoin.

The price of Bitcoin attracted me, the value behind Bitcoin holds me. Even though there is probably a capitalist in all of us: should Bitcoin ever fail - for whatever reason - and every part of those 21,000,000 units of absolute scarcity fall to 0, I never regret my decision to have learned about Bitcoin, to have taken time, to have understood it, to have called it my property, and to have shown it to my fellow human beings.

The personality development, the insights, the brilliant relationships with people from all over the world who think and feel the same way are more valuable than any amount of money. To stand up for something with heart and humanity alone, which is probably the only thing that can still help the world, should make us all proud.

You don't need to be ashamed of something or be afraid of it if it is as human as Bitcoin. Even if it were to fail.

Keep going everyone, keep spreading Bitcoin. Your work is immeasurably important to the world and the universe will repay you 1000 fold.

cleaned_data.original_text:
It's time to break down exactly how this new #Bitcoin price model works...

As I said this is derived from my November 28th Cycles Theory.

This Theory calls tops and bottoms with a +/- 21 day accuracy and tells us what happens in each given year

Tops and bottoms come at these dates:

Tops = +/- 21 days from Nov 28th end of red year (red dots)

Bottoms = +/- 21 days from Nov 28th beginning of green year (green dots)

The model starts on the day of the first halving, Nov 28th 2012.

Cycles have formed in between each date of Nov 28th.

Let's get into what happens during each year based on my N28CT and this price model:

Green year (Accumulation) = Bitcoin forms a bottom at the beginning of the year +/- 28 days from Nov 28th. This is the year of the best cycle buying prices, and the best time to accumulate. 

Price also moves towards the median price. (half of previous ATH). This is the first price that can be predicted labeled with blue lines, and their blue dot when price touches it.

Blue Year (Preparation for New ATHs) = Bitcoin spends time around the blue line (median), and then makes an advance towards new ATHs (small red line).

Red Year (New ATHs) = Price makes new ATHs during this year. Bitcoin follows the red trends outlined according to their diminishing pattern. This has been 70, 60, and 50 degrees in order for cycles so far. Implying the next would be 40 and 30.

Price makes its cycle top +/- 21 days from Nov 28th at the end of the year.

Orange Year (Bear Market) = After becoming over-valuated at the cycle high, Bitcoin moves to undervaluation. On this scale, this has always been at a 44-degree descent. We can then find the next cycle bottom price using this measurement, which will come at the end of the year.

Using this model give us these predictions:

Cycle Top Price 2025: 140k

Cycle Bottom Price 2026: $27,000

Median Price Next Cycle: 70k

Cycle Top Price 2029: 190k

Cycle Bottom Price 2030: 36k

Many people don't like to hear these prices, sorry. It's the results of the model. If the prices were higher they would show on the chart.

Each target is judged strictly according to the angle sequences.

I know you all have probably heard some pretty outlandish targets over the years, the Bitcoin community does a great job of that.

Reflect back and think how many there were last cycle! How did that pan out?

Same arguments, institutional adoption and scarcity. I heard that a lot when I was selling all my Bitcoin at 54k in April 2021.

Here's something else I'll tell you most people won't... don't go and blindly follow this model. 

Always use data from many sources to come to conclusions! Setting price targets dooms you to fail. They are for speculation and possibilities, not financial decisions.

Remember how many people were lost looking for 100k last cycle top. What happened to them?

Here's a last question for you to think on, are you prepared if that happens again? I am!

#Bitcoin is back to blue! 

During major bull runs, miner revenue begins a huge ramp up while prices surge.

These times in the red can only come after cool down and accumulation in blue low pressure.
                                                    
After sending a huge false spike in 2-year miner revenue fees due to ordinals, Bitcoin has returned to its low fee pressure accumulation mode.

This was the same thing that happened in 2019, after a big parabolic run up to the mid-top of $14,000 with a smaller red spike in revenue.

Our time in the true red bull run will come again!

Short-Term #Bitcoin holders are losing big, with their profit plummeting to lows not seen since the bear market downtrend during 2022.

At first glance, this looks like a bad thing.
               
Short-Term Holder Profit only drops this low at the start of a bear market... but a closer look shows us this same thing happened in 2019, after the major early run.

Were it not for the 2020 black swan, the profit floor likely would have marked the bottom then.

A touch of the profit floor now may be the last chance that many would get to buy at the best prices of the cycle, and that's not far away!

#Bitcoin is starting to dip its toes back into the orange hope/fear range of the NUPL.

First, the NUPL tells us that the lows for the cycle are in, and there's no looking back after the deep retrace into red capitulation.
                             
After this happens, Bitcoin has always surged to yellow optimism/anxiety, and taken one or two final dips into orange hope/fear.

This is where we are now.

Most of Bitcoin's time will be spent in yellow, this development in orange, once completed, could be a final opportunity.

Behind the scenes, when you buy, sell, send or receive #Bitcoin, you're doing it in a larger chunk than you write down.

Some of it is then given back to you, like change. This is a UTXO. (Unspent Transaction Output)
       
This "change" is in extremely heavy loss, not seen since the 2020 Black Swan.

An event like this has happened each cycle, where UTXO's in loss skyrockets and makes "the bottom after the bottom".

It looks like the last stop before the bull run is now developing!

cleaned_data.original_text:
Is #Bitcoin  overvalued? Let's see:

19,471,000 Bitcoin are in circulation. At currently $29,000 per Bitcoin, that makes ~$545.2 billion equivalent in US dollars.

While it came to this number, 805,352 Bitcoin blocks were added to the Genesis Block since early 2009. Over a period of nearly 15 years, increasingly more energy, time and resources have been devoted to the Bitcoin network every single minute by more and more people around the world, to in the end adding up to just 0.178% of the value of the current global debt of ~$305 trillion, caused by a broken monetary system.

The Bitcoin network right now is worth 0.178% of the worlds total debt. These are just the ratios to global debt.

Again, is Bitcoin overvalued?

When you understand how uniquely Bitcoin works, which is in a decentralized way perfectly sophisticated symbiosis of many individual components working together like Swiss clockwork finely tuned hand in hand, all backed by physics and mathematics, which is the language of the universe and energy is its currency, then you realize almost in awe how light years away Bitcoin must be from the word 'overvalued'.

Bitcoin is so ridiculously undervalued that it is always worth buying Bitcoin - no matter when.

And besides: financial freedom is the smallest reason to own Bitcoin. The weight of these words becomes heavier every day.

cleaned_data.original_text:
Bitcoin Spot ETFs are potentially VERY BAD for security, long term.

Let me explain something:

Bitcoin (the network) currently pays 6.25 $BTC (the token or coin) every ~10 minutes, which then gets distributed by mining pools 99% of the time.

(it has been REALLY HARD to win a full Bitcoin block by "solo mining" for a long time)

In the year 2140, Bitcoin will experience a final halving event. 

But if you look at the inflation chart below then you should see the practical reality: 

Bitcoin could stop being profitable to mine based on the block reward alone MUCH sooner than that.

What helps maintain profitability?

Fees.

Bottom-Line-Up-Front (BLUF) is that as the block reward decreases, ONE of the biggest recent factors in Bitcoin's economic incentive for SECURITY ("mining") is fees.

Transactions generate fees.

Minting ordinal inscriptions generate fees.

On-chain DeFi (sites like @NOWPFinance) generates fees.

All of these fees are added to the current 6.25 BTC payout to give incentive to the world to absolutely CRUSH the hashrate of Bitcoin, and spend an increasing amount of effort into solving more hashes.

Know what DOESN'T give Bitcoin's layer 1 network fees?

Off-chain orderbooks.

CEX's, escrows, and (taps glass) ETFs.

All of these remove transaction volume from Bitcoin's layer 1, which 100% DELETES the built-in fee incentive.

"But Seth, an ETF will usher in mass adoption!"

OK, so you want decreased security funding, and you want it AT SCALE?

(BTW this is the same fundamental problem of Lightning Network or @ElonMusk's previous offer to shift DOGE to proof of stake)

So, the more adoption a Bitcoin Spot ETF receives, the LESS SECURE the native asset- Bitcoin- becomes.

"But Seth, isn't that priced in? Won't Bitcoin's price appreciation make the decreased fees palatable to miners?"

No.

Because it will substantially decrease the number of fees actually paid (fully DELETING the majority of them) and in ways we can't forecast very well.

Bitcoin security has absolutely gone through some rough patches- MANY entities have folded/gone bankrupt over building too much mining infrastructure too soon.

I LIKE the idea of price discovery & appreciation.
I WANT to be financially free because of my good habits in crypto.

But, like most people, I NEED for Bitcoin to be sustainably secure more than I need it to make me accidentally rich.
-----------------------------------------------
If this was helpful, consider signing up for my FREE "21 Lessons" series at https://t.co/WyDeVcEnup

Look for 10 year horizons: #BTC is the answer. 

If you had $1 million in a global 60/40 portfolio back in 2015, it would have grown to approximately $2.21M by the end of 2022.

If you had chosen a more “unconventional” route and invested $1 million in a portfolio consisting of 15% #Bitcoin and 85% USD in 2015, your portfolio would have grown to a staggering $5M by the end of 2022 without considering the run from the start of 2023.

Imagine 40%? 50%? 60%?

Calculations for #BTC :

Starting with $1 million in 2015, with 15% ($150,000) in Bitcoin:

•In 2015, the Bitcoin portion would grow by 35% to $202,500.
•In 2016, it would grow by 125% to $455,625.
•In 2017, it would grow by 1,331% to about $6.54 million.
•In 2018, it would shrink by 73% to about $1.77 million.
•In 2019, it would grow by 95% to about $3.45 million.
•In 2020, it would grow by 301% to about $13.84 million.
•In 2021, it would grow by 90% to about $26.3 million.
•In 2022, it would shrink by 81.02% to about $4.99 million.

We will see in 2023? 2024? 2025? 2026?

Thoughts? 🤔

cleaned_data.original_text:
The mathematical significance of 1 #Bitcoin  in relation to time is huge. Let me show you why:

First, it is interesting to know how much 1 Bitcoin represents in percentage terms measured against the total amount of Bitcoin ever available.

1/21,000,000 equals 0.0000000476%, very little. However, Bitcoin has something ingenious embedded in it. With the halving epochs, time takes on a special role for Bitcoin:

In the first period, 50 Bitcoin are created every 10 minutes on average, 600 seconds, or 1 Bitcoin every 12 seconds. Every 12 seconds 0.0000000476% of the total supply.

Today in 2023, there are 6.25 new Bitcoin every 600 seconds, or 1 Bitcoin per 96 seconds. Every 96 seconds 0.0000000476% of the total. When the fourth halving arrives in a few months, it will take 192 seconds - 3 minutes and 12 seconds - for each new Bitcoin.

When will the time come that 1 year must pass before 1 Bitcoin is created?

Let's jump to 2092: the block subsidy is 0.0001192 Bitcoin. It will take more than a year to find a full Bitcoin: 1/0.0001192 = 83,893 blocks ≈ 838,930 minutes ≈ 1.6 years. Just over 2 Bitcoin are issued in this halving period.

The same amount of new value that is created today in just 96 seconds, will ~68 years later take over a year and a half to be created.

But Bitcoin shows us its full potential of the inflation plan the closer we get to the total amount: if only 0.0000000476% - i.e. the last Bitcoin - is missing, it will take about 35 years until this last Bitcoin becomes usable for mankind.

What started with 12 seconds in 2009 will reach its zenith in 2140, when from the years 2104/2106 on, ~35 years of time are needed to create the last full Bitcoin.

With each halving, the period until a new Bitcoin is created doubles. It will become increasingly difficult, incredibly difficult for anyone to obtain fresh Bitcoin as time progresses.

Horrible things like man made devastating wars will hardly be feasible and affordable anymore, because Bitcoin is simply too rare to be able and willing to wage war with it.

In the long run it needs mathematics to create peace, because man alone will probably never be able to do it.

Modern man: finally embrace the beauty of mathematics. The beauty of Bitcoin.

US national debt: ~$32.5 trillion.
Bitcoin market capitalization: ~$0.5 trillion.
The US national debt is a factor of 65 higher than the dollar value of all available Bitcoin.

When I read or hear about being late with Bitcoin, but you couldn't even pay off 2% of the United States of America's debt with all the Bitcoin in the world right now, I have to smile.

We are only talking about the debt of one country. 21,000,000 Bitcoin meets everything in the known world.

Bitcoin is incredibly underpriced. You can't even imagine it. In a world where numbers, paper money and credit are getting bigger, more frequent and more arbitrary, the world ever more hectic, chaotic and opaque, there has been a pulse of calm for nearly 15 years. Working like a compass in this ocean of noise and haphazardness.

Bitcoin's inflation is getting lower and lower, soon below 1%, even lower than gold. The amount per person is getting scarcer and scarcer. It's been hair-trigger verifiable and measurable for eternity since the first second what numbers we'll be dealing with. The die is cast.

Bitcoin is an architectural masterpiece of physics and mathematics chiseled into the hardest construct in the universe.

If you're not even going to be late in 10 years, how can you be today?
